# OSI(Open Systems Interconnection) Model
a reference multi-level model for describing and defining interactions between systems (consists of 7 levels). Was created to visualize the structure and establish connections

| Layer | Function |
|-------|----------|
| 7.Application | manages data input and output and provides application functionality |
| 6.Presentation | converting data into an application-independent form |
| 5.Session | manages the logical connection between two systems and prevents various connection problems |
| 4.Transport | end-to-end control of the transferred data |
| 3.Network | establishes a connection and sends data |
| 2.Data Link | reliable and error-free data transmission (bit streams are divided into frames or blocks) |
| 1.Physical | transmission is carried out via wired or wireless communication lines |

layers 2-4 - transport oriented, layers 5-7 - application oriented
